Bloodveld can be found in the God Wars Dungeon. They can be fought for kill count for the Zamorak faction.

Equipping a Zamorak insignia makes them non aggressive.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 11 September 2023 (Update):
    • Increased drop rate of congealed blood at Gargoyles, Nechyraels, Bloodvelds and Terror dogs to reduce reliance on Ravenous Ghouls
  • patch 16 January 2017 (Update):
    • Bloodvelds are now all melee-based and weak to fire spells.
  • patch 18 August 2014 (Update):
    • Bloodvelds in the Slayer Tower, Godwards[sic] and Morytania's Underground have now had their models updated.
  • update 26 January 2005 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Bloodveld are loyal to Zamorak, as shown in the God Wars Dungeon and Heart of Gielinor.
  • The examine text of bloodveld is similar to other slayer monsters. The bloodveld is "the tongue of evil", the dust devil is "the vacuumed face of evil", the basilisk is "the eyes of evil" and the rockslug "the slime of evil."
  • The bloodveld seems to attack twice in a row but it only attacks once, as seen on the hitsplats.
  • Vampyres keep bloodveld as pets, in a similar fashion to the way in which humans keep dogs. Harold, who belongs to Vanstrom Klause is one example, as are Grigan Kaninus' bloodveld younglings.
  • In the Postbag from the Hedge 12, their tongues are likened to that of KISS bassist Gene Simmons, a rock star who himself has an unusually long tongue.
  • On 16 January 2017, their attack style and weakness were changed from magic and thrown weapons to melee and fire spells, respectively.
  • As of 1 February 2018, the highest kill count for this monster was 80,366 kills.[1]
    • This had not increased by 6 May 2018.[2]
